      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A font descriptor can be used to create or modify a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifont"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object. Font descriptors have a font matching capability, so that you can partially describe a font by creating a font descriptor with, for example, just a family name. You can use  "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616699-matchingfontdescriptorswithmanda"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to find all the available fonts in the system with a matching family name. Font descriptors can also be archived and unarchived. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "There are several ways to create a new "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object. To take advantage of text styles and respect the userâ€™s current content size category, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616705-preferredfontdescriptorwithtexts"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". You can also use "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "alloc"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and  "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616679-initwithfontattributes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616717-fontdescriptorwithfontattributes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616670-fontdescriptorwithname"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616674-fontdescriptorwithname"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to create a font descriptor based on your custom attributes dictionary or on a specific fontâ€™s name and size. Alternatively you can use one of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "fontDescriptorâ€¦"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance methods (such as "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontdescriptor/1616681-fontdescriptorwithface"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") to create a modified version of an existing descriptor. The latter methods are useful if you have an existing descriptor and simply want to change one aspect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "All attributes in the attributes dictionary are optional."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For design guidance, see "
            },
